FT  18 MAR 93 / UK Company News: S Daniels improves in second half
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Improved trading in the second six months at S Daniels, an importer and
distributor for the food industry, resulted in a reduced pre-tax loss of
Pounds 64,000 for 1992, compared with Pounds 105,000 in the first six months
and Pounds 158,000 in 1991.
The results have been prepared under the FRS 3 accounting principles.
Turnover of continuing operations increased from Pounds 29.8m to Pounds
32.3m.
The loss was struck after a Pounds 101,000 deficit on disposal of
discontinued operations, less a 1991 provision of Pounds 110,000.
The dividend is held at 0.25p. Losses per share were halved to 1p.
