<TEXT>
JAMES FISHER, the Cumbria-based shipping group, yesterday accompanied
sharply reduced annual profit and dividend with a gloomy statement on
current trading.
Despite a reduced deficit of Pounds 1m (Pounds 1.99m) from port operations,
a lower contribution from the shipping side of Pounds 2.97m (Pounds 3.8m)
and interest payable of Pounds 1.06m (Pounds 674,251) left the pre-tax line
