FT  18 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Spandex rises 6% to Pounds 4.46m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spandex, which distributes and supplies signmaking computers and materials,
raised pre-tax profits by 6 per cent from Pounds 4.2m to Pounds 4.46m in
1992, on sales also 6 per cent higher at Pounds 55m.
Earnings per share rose from 20.4p to 22.5p, while a final dividend of 4.6p
makes a total for the year of 6.5p (6p).
Mr Charles Dobson, chairman of the USM-traded group, said net debt had been
reduced from Pounds 7.2m at the end of 1991 to Pounds 4.3m at December 31
1992, thereby reducing gearing from 56 per cent to 29 per cent.
