FT  17 MAR 93 / World Trade News: Peugeot forms Indian venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By WILLIAM DAWKINS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Peugeot, the French carmaker, has overtaken Italian and Japanese competition
to strike an agreement in principle for a joint venture with the Indian car
group, Premier Automobiles, William Dawkins reports from Paris.
Peugeot and Premier Automobiles have signed a memorandum of understanding to
set up an equally owned car assembly company in India, to produce Peugeot
vehicles in 12 to 18 months from now. The joint venture will assemble around
60,000 cars annually at first. The partners are still finalising the choice
of models.
