<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Spirax-Sarco in Pounds 5.4m disposal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Spirax-Sarco Engineering has sold two subsidiaries, Drayton Controls
(Engineering) and Oreg Drayton Energietechnik, to Unitech for a total cash
consideration of Pounds 5.4m.
The businesses manufacture a range of automatic temperature and time
controls for the domestic central heating market in the UK and Germany, a
market that does not figure in Spirax-Sarco's long term strategy.
For the year to end-December 1992 the businesses made pre-tax profits of
Pounds 650,000.
The book value of the assets being sold amounts to Pounds 6.3m.
