<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / Revenue writes off Pounds 900m unpaid tax
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID OWEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE INLAND Revenue wrote off nearly Pounds 900m in unpaid taxes in 1991  -
an increase of 55 per cent on 1990.
The disclosure, covering the latest year for which figures are available,
came in a written Commons answer from Mr Stephen Dorrell, financial
secretary to the Treasury.
The sum written off in 1990 totalled nearly Pounds 569m, he indicated in a
reply to Mr Archie Kirkwood, the Liberal Democrat MP for Roxburgh and
Berwickshire.
In a separate answer, Mr Dorrell disclosed that an independent survey in
June 1992 suggested that one in three employed taxpayers were dissatisfied
with service from the Inland Revenue.
Research International, a market research group, found that only 65 per cent
of employed and self-employed taxpayers were satisfied.
</TEXT>
