<TEXT>
PRESIDENT Bill Clinton yesterday told Father Jean-Bertrand Aristide, exiled
Haitian president, that he would not now issue a formal ultimatum to the
military regime demanding that the country's legitimate government be
restored by a given date, writes Jurek Martin in Washington.
But he is sending a special envoy to Port-au-Prince to tell the coup leaders
that US patience is wearing thin. The administration is furious with the
human rights abuses of the Haitian regime, but it also has misgivings about
Fr Aristide's democratic credentials.
