<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Plan to widen VAT relief
 -Training
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This section contains details of the government's planned tax changes which
were given in separate announcements from the Inland Revenue, Customs and
Excise and other government departments after the chancellor had made his
publication of the Budget details in the Finance Bill.
THE VAT relief available to training providers participating in
government-funded training programmes is to be widened under Budget
proposals.
From April 1 supplies of all such training, including the provision of work
experience, will be exempt.
The chancellor aims to minimise the effect of VAT on government-funded
training and to introduce greater uniformity in tax treatment.
Training providers affected by the change will need to consider how it
affects their tax status.
Some may make only exempt provision, in which case they will be unable to
reclaim any input tax but they will no longer need to be registered. Other
training may become partially exempt, in which case providers will no longer
be able to reclaim all their input tax.
The changes will be made by way of the Value Added Tax (Education) Order
1993. The estimated revenue effect is an annual loss of around Pounds 25m.
The chancellor proposes to exempt from tax the value of outplacement
services provided to employees.
This will apply to employees made redundant yesterday or after, or to
outplacement services bought from yesterday onward. The proposal is that:
counselling services provided to employees who are, or become redundant,
will be exempt from income tax; employers paying for counselling services
for these employees will get a tax deduction for these payments.
The intention is to improve labour market flexibility. The measure responds
to widespread representations, particularly from employers' representative
bodies and from employees themselves.
The proposal will allow employers to provide outplacement services free of
tax, whether or not the total redundancy package is worth more than Pounds
30,000.
</TEXT>
