<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): 'Capital loss buying'
curb
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE BUDGET includes proposals to restrict the set off of capital losses
brought into a group of companies as the result of a company joining the
group. Losses set off against gains arising on or after yesterday will be
restricted where they came from a company which joined the group after 31
March 1987.
The chancellor's intention is to curtail 'capital loss buying' - a practice
used by groups to reduce tax liability on capital gains. It involves buying
in losses from other companies which have nothing to do with the purchasing
group's own efforts or activities, and getting the benefit of tax relief on
the losses even though the group has not suffered the loss.
</TEXT>
