<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Bad debt relief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
From 1 April traders will be able to claim relief on any debt which has been
written off after six months, which is changed from a year.
The intention is to provide an immediate boost to businesses' cash flow
estimated at Pounds 150m in 1993-94. The reduction in the waiting period
should mean that relief is available swiftly on all bad debts, said Customs
and Excise.
</TEXT>
