<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Cash accounting
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The turnover limit for companies using the cash accounting scheme is being
raised from Pounds 300,000 to Pounds 350,000 a year from 1 April.
Companies joining the scheme will no longer be required to make a written
application to Customs and Excise. A consultation document has been issued
inviting comments on how the operation of the scheme could be made more
attractive to businesses and simpler to use.
</TEXT>
