<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Triangular transactions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Simplification procedures will apply to some commercial transactions which
involve traders from other member states of the European Community from
August 1.
These changes are for 'triangular' transactions when commercial goods are
supplied in a chain involving three traders located in different member
states, but where physical delivery of the goods involves their movement
direct from the first member state to the third; and goods installed or
assembled in the UK by traders from other EC countries.
The intention is to give legal effect to an EC-wide scheme aimed at reducing
the need for intermediate suppliers to register for Vat in the country where
the goods are delivered.
</TEXT>
