<HEADLINE>
FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Valuation allowance for
share disposals - Rollover relief
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This section contains details of the government's planned tax changes which
were given in separate announcements from the Inland Revenue, Customs and
Excise and other government departments after the chancellor had made his
publication of the Budget details in the Finance Bill.
IT IS proposed to add new EC agricultural quotas for the premium given to
producers of ewes and suckler cows to the list of assets which qualify for
capital gains tax rollover relief. In addition the chancellor proposes a
general power to add, by Treasury order, to the list of assets which qualify
for rollover relief.
The proposals recognise the fact that, since such quotas can be capital
assets of farming trades, rollover relief should be available for them.
The changes will apply to acquisitions and disposals on or after January 1
1993.
On the valuation of shares the Inland Revenue has issued an extra-statutory
concession relating to the calculation of March 31 1982 values of shares and
securities for capital gains tax rebasing and indexation purposes.
The concession will allow individuals and companies disposing of shares
acquired from their spouse or a company in the same group owning the shares
at March 31 1982 the choice of adopting a more favourable basis of valuation
at that date.
The concession applies to a disposal of shares which an individual has
acquired on a no gain/no loss transfer from a husband or wife who held the
shares on March 31 1982 or which a company has acquired on a no gain/no loss
transfer from a company in the same group which held the shares on March 31
1982.
For indexation and rebasing purposes the individual or company is treated as
having held the transferred shares on March 31 1982. They are added to any
shares the taxpayer actually held on March 31 1982 and all the shares are
valued as a single holding.
This may have the effect of lowering the March 31 1982 market value of the
shares in the hands of the transferee.
</TEXT>
