FT  17 MAR 93 / The Budget (Government Statements): Tighter rules on
pensions
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
This section contains details of the government's planned tax changes which
were given in separate announcements from the Inland Revenue, Customs and
Excise and other government departments after the chancellor had made his
publication of the Budget details in the Finance Bill.
THE chancellor also announced measures aimed at ensuring that tax relief to
approved occupational pension schemes is given only when contributions are
actually paid into pension schemes.
The Inland Revenue said its long-standing view of the law was 'that an
employer may have a deduction from profits for tax purposes only for sums
paid into an approved occupational pension scheme'. Doubt has recently been
cast on this view particularly following a Statement of Standard Accounting
Practice (SSAP 24) issued in 1988.
